-- Market Chatter- Corporate finance press digest
-- 
-- Thu Jan 23, 2014 11:12PM EST
-- None



Jan 24 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* India's Bharti Airtel <BRTI.NS> plans to sell most of its transmitter towers in Africa, in a process that could raise up to $2 billion for the country's top telecom operator and help reduce its debt.[ID:nL5N0KX322]  * Bidders for the oil and gas exploration offshoot of German utility RWE AG <RWEG.DE> value the unit in a wide range between 3.5 billion euros ($4.8 billion) and 5 billion, two sources familiar with the transaction said on Thursday.[ID:nL5N0KW1JM] * T. Rowe Price Group <TROW.O> sent a letter this week to Time Warner Cable <TWC.N> urging the cable company to have talks with smaller cable provider Charter <CHTR.O> about a possible deal, according to people familiar with the matter.[ID:nL2N0KX1MN]  * Britain may announce an order for 14 Lockheed Martin-built <LMT.N> F-35 super-stealth jets as early as next week, three sources familiar with the talks told Reuters.[ID:nL5N0KX2ZA]  * Activist investor Carl Icahn's stake in e-commerce company eBay Inc <EBAY.O> is more than previously reported at close to 2 percent, a source familiar with the matter said on Thursday. [ID:nL2N0KY00X]  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]